## Basic Nano Configuration

# Set tab size to 4 spaces (adjust according to your coding style)
set tabsize 4

# Convert typed tabs into spaces â€“ useful for consistent indentation in code
set tabstospaces

# Do not wrap long lines; you can remove or comment this if you prefer wrapping
#set nowrap

# Automatically indent new lines based on the previous line's indentation
set autoindent

# Create backup files (adds a ~ to the filename) to help prevent accidental data loss
#set backup

# Always show the cursor position, file name, and other status info in the status bar
set constantshow

# Display line numbers on the left-hand side for easier navigation
set linenumbers

# Enable mouse support for scrolling and cursor positioning
set mouse